{{cot|Specified coordinates examples}}
Point feature (with coordinates specified, no shape/line feature from Wikidata item):
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{infobox mapframe |coord={{coord|31|56|S|115|58|E}} }}</syntaxhighlight>
{{infobox mapframe |id=Q45935 |coord={{coord|31|56|S|115|58|E}} }}
Point feature (with coordinates specified, along with shape/line feature from Wikidata item):
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{infobox mapframe |wikidata=yes |coord={{coord|31|56|S|115|58|E}} }}</syntaxhighlight>
{{infobox mapframe |id=Q45935 |wikidata=yes |coord={{coord|31|56|S|115|58|E}} }}
{{cob}}

===Customizing which features are displayed===
====Inverse shape====
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |shape=inverse}}</syntaxhighlight>
Replace the shape with an inverse-shape (geomask) by setting {{para|shape|inverse}}
{{cot|Inverse shape example}}
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q61 |shape=inverse}}</syntaxhighlight>
{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q61 |shape=inverse}}
{{cob}}

====Turn point marker on or off====
Force point marker to be displayed:
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |point=on}}</syntaxhighlight>
Prevent point marker from being displayed:
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |point=none}}</syntaxhighlight>

====Turn shape feature off====
Prevent shape feature from being displayed:
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |shape=none}}</syntaxhighlight>

====Turn line feature off====
Prevent line feature from being displayed:
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |line=none}}</syntaxhighlight>

===Show a geomask from a related Wikidata item===
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |geomask=}}</syntaxhighlight>
Set {{para|geomask}} to a Wikidata item id (Q-number), or property id (P-number) such as {{Q|P17}}
{{cot|Geomask examples}}
Use the item linked from the {{q|P17}} statement as a geomask:
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q3239281 |geomask=P17}}</syntaxhighlight>
{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q3239281 |geomask=P17}}
Use the item {{q|Q1199}} as a geomask:
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q3239281 |geomask=Q1199}}</syntaxhighlight>
{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q3239281 |geomask=Q1199}}
{{cob}}

===Determine zoom from object length or area===
Use any of the following parameters to specify an object's dimension:
{{col div|colwidth=15em}}
*{{para|length_km}}
*{{para|length_mi}}
*{{para|width_km}}
*{{para|width_mi}}
*{{para|area_km2}}
*{{para|area_mi2}}
*{{para|area_ha}}
*{{para|area_acre}}
{{col div end}}

Additionally, the zoom of the mapframe can be set by specifying the {{para|type}} of the object, with the same usage as {{tl|coord}}. For example, {{para|type|city}}. In the case of a city, the population can determine the zoom by specifying {{para|population}}.
{{cot|Zoom from length/area examples}}
Determine zoom from object length in kilometres or miles
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q1318331 |length_km=5.6}}</syntaxhighlight>
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q1318331 |length_mi=3.5}}</syntaxhighlight>
{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q1318331 |length_km=5.6}}
Determine zoom from object area in square kilometres or square miles
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q100 |area_km2=232.14}}</syntaxhighlight>
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q100 |area_mi2=89.63}}</syntaxhighlight>
{{Infobox mapframe |id=Q100 |area_km2=232.14}}
{{cob}}

==Parameters==
All parameters are optional.

{{Infobox mapframe/doc/parameters|noprefix=yes|deprecated=yes}}

